snippet.title: ANACONDA – Official Trailer (HD)
snippet.description:
I like big snakes and I cannot lie. Paul Rudd and Jack Black star in #AnacondaMovie – exclusively in theatres Christmas.

Follow Us on Social:
https://x.com/Anaconda_Movie
https://www.facebook.com/AnacondaMovie
https://www.tiktok.com/@anacondamovie
https://www.instagram.com/anacondamovie

Visit our site: https://anacondamovie.com/

Subscribe for more exclusive content: https://www.youtube.com/@sonypictures

Doug (Jack Black) and Griff (Paul Rudd) have been best friends since they were kids, and have always dreamed of remaking their all-time favorite movie: the cinematic "classic" Anaconda. When a midlife crisis pushes them to finally go for it, they head deep into the Amazon to start filming. But things get real when an actual giant anaconda appears, turning their comically chaotic movie set into a deadly situation. The movie they’re dying to make? It might just get them killed

Tom Gormican​

snippet.title: SUGAR SUPREME POWER NUDGE | FIRST LOOK
snippet.description:
In this BSBZA video I try out Sugar Supreme Power Nudge for the very first time, and it did not disappoint. This new release takes the sweet and colourful world that fans of Sugar Rush will already know and love, and gives it a twist with the Power Nudge mechanic, making the gameplay feel fresh, fast, and packed with potential.

I kicked off the session by mixing both normal spins and bonus buys, testing out how the game works in practice and whether the new mechanics make a real difference. Sugar Supreme is built on a 6×6 grid and uses cluster pays, so instead of traditional paylines, wins are formed by landing clusters of matching symbols. The standout feature here is the Power Nudge, where after a winning cluster lands, the reels nudge down to potentially create new wins from the same spin. This keeps the action going and can chain together some huge results if the right clusters drop in sequence.

Another big part of the game is the multiplier system. Multipliers are attached to reels, and with every Power Nudge, those multipliers increase. The longer the nudges continue, the higher the multipliers climb, and this is where the game can go from exciting to absolutely explosive. In the Free Spins feature, those multipliers don’t reset, meaning they just keep building throughout the round, giving the potential for massive returns.

What makes Sugar Supreme Power Nudge stand out is the combination of sticky multipliers and continuous reel nudges. It’s high volatility, which means the base game can be tough, but when everything lines up in the free spins round, it feels like anything is possible. In this first look session, I give my honest thoughts on how it compares to games like Sugar Rush, whether the Power Nudge makes it more entertaining, and how it fits into the Pragmatic Play library.

If you enjoy fast-paced, high-risk gameplay with unique mechanics, you’ll want to watch this video to the end. Sugar Supreme Power Nudge is one of those titles that can completely flip a session with one good feature, and I got a real taste of that in this first run.

Don’t forget to let me know in the comments if you’ve played it yet, and subscribe to BSBZA for more first look sessions, big game challenges, and community-driven episodes
